.TH set_term 3
.SH NAME
\*Lset_term\*O \- Switches between terminals
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*LSCREEN \(**set_term(\*Vnew\*L)
    SCREEN \(**\*Vnew\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "set_term subroutine"
This routine is used to switch between different terminals.
The screen reference \*Lnew\*O becomes the new current terminal.
The previous terminal screen reference is returned by the routine.
.PP
This is the only routine which manipulates SCREEN
pointers; all the others change the current terminal only.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lset_term\*O function returns a pointer to the
previous SCREEN structure on success and a null pointer on error.
.EQ
